4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING THAT THE DEPRIVATION OF THE RIGHT TO KEEP
5 AND BEAR ARMS WHEN CHARGED WITH CERTAIN CRIMES IS PROHIBITED; AND PROVIDING AN
6 EXCEPTION FOR FORCIBLE FELONIES AND CRIMES USING A WEAPON.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Deprivation of right to keep and bear arms prohibited -- exceptions.
11 Except when a person is charged with committing a forcible felony as defined in 45-2-101 or charged with a
12 crime of violence using a weapon as defined in 45-2-101, a person may not be deprived, pending trial, of any
13 rights protected by Article II, section 12, of the Montana constitution or the second amendment to the United
14 States constitution.
